FUNCTION: mat_copy_column

DESCRIPTION: Copy a column of a matrix

REQUIRES: ---

BUGS: ---

FUTURE IMPROVEMENTS: ---

----------------------------------------------------------------------

PROCESS DESCRIPTION:

  mat_copy_column(addr_srcMat:EAX,
                  addr_dstMat:EBX,
                  numOfRows:ECX,
                  rowSize:EDX)

  Input parameters
      1) addr_srcMat = Address to the source matrix
      2) addr_dstMat = Address to the destination matrix
      3) numOfRows   = Number of rows for both matrix
      4) rowSize     = Size of a row for both matrix

  Output parameters
      2) addr_dstMat = Filled with data from source matrix column

  Returns
      ---

  +-------------------------------------------------------------+
  |                   STACK MEMORY INFORMATION                  |
  +--------+----------------------------------------------------+
  | Offset |      Data       |           Description            |
  +--------+-----------------+----------------------------------+
  | +    0 | ---             | ---                              |
  |        |                 |                                  |
  +--------+-----------------+----------------------------------+
  | Total stack used for local variables =  0 bytes             |
  +-------------------------------------------------------------+

  Algorithm/Pseudocode is in "scilab/mat_copy_column.sce"

